@startuml SD_14_DashboardAnalytics
' ============================================================
' SEQUENCE DIAGRAM - Dashboard & Thống kê
' FR-37~FR-39: Organizer/Admin/Staff Dashboard
' ============================================================

title **SD-14: Dashboard & Thống kê\n(Analytics for Organizer/Admin/Staff)**

skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam roundcorner 10
skinparam sequence {
    ParticipantBackgroundColor #E8EAF6
    ParticipantBorderColor #283593
    ArrowColor #283593
}

actor "Organizer" as Organizer #Gold
participant "Browser" as Browser #LightYellow
participant "DashboardServlet\n(Controller)" as Controller #E8EAF6
participant "DashboardService" as DashSvc #E8F5E9
participant "EventDAO" as EvtDAO #FFF3E0
participant "OrderDAO" as OrdDAO #FFF3E0
participant "TicketDAO" as TktDAO #FFF3E0
database "SQL Server" as DB #F3E5F5

== Organizer Dashboard ==

Organizer -> Browser: Truy cập Dashboard
Browser -> Controller: GET /organizer/dashboard
activate Controller

' --- KPI 1: Event Stats ---
Controller -> DashSvc: getOrganizerStats(organizerId)
activate DashSvc

DashSvc -> EvtDAO: countByOrganizer(orgId)
activate EvtDAO
EvtDAO -> DB: SELECT status,\nCOUNT(*) as count\nFROM Events\nWHERE organizerId = ?\nGROUP BY status
activate DB
DB --> EvtDAO: {pending:2, approved:10,\nrejected:1, cancelled:0}
deactivate DB
EvtDAO --> DashSvc: event counts
deactivate EvtDAO

' --- KPI 2: Revenue ---
DashSvc -> OrdDAO: getRevenueByOrganizer(orgId)
activate OrdDAO
OrdDAO -> DB: SELECT \n  SUM(o.totalAmount) as totalRevenue,\n  COUNT(o.orderId) as totalOrders,\n  SUM(o.eventDiscountAmount) as discounts\nFROM Orders o\nJOIN Events e ON o.eventId = e.eventId\nWHERE e.organizerId = ?\nAND o.status = 'confirmed'
activate DB
DB --> OrdDAO: {totalRevenue: 15000000,\ntotalOrders: 120, discounts: 500000}
deactivate DB
OrdDAO --> DashSvc: revenue stats
deactivate OrdDAO

' --- KPI 3: Ticket Sales ---
DashSvc -> TktDAO: getSalesStats(orgId)
activate TktDAO
TktDAO -> DB: SELECT \n  COUNT(t.ticketId) as totalTickets,\n  SUM(CASE WHEN t.isCheckedIn=1\n    THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) as checkedIn\nFROM Tickets t\nJOIN Orders o ON t.orderId = o.orderId\nJOIN Events e ON o.eventId = e.eventId\nWHERE e.organizerId = ?\nAND o.status = 'confirmed'
activate DB
DB --> TktDAO: {totalTickets: 350,\ncheckedIn: 180}
deactivate DB
TktDAO --> DashSvc: ticket stats
deactivate TktDAO

' --- KPI 4: Revenue Chart (7 days) ---
DashSvc -> OrdDAO: getRevenueByDay(orgId, 7)
activate OrdDAO
OrdDAO -> DB: SELECT \n  CAST(o.paymentDate AS DATE) as day,\n  SUM(o.totalAmount) as revenue,\n  COUNT(*) as orders\nFROM Orders o\nJOIN Events e ON o.eventId = e.eventId\nWHERE e.organizerId = ?\nAND o.status = 'confirmed'\nAND o.paymentDate >= DATEADD(day,-7,GETDATE())\nGROUP BY CAST(o.paymentDate AS DATE)\nORDER BY day
activate DB
DB --> OrdDAO: [{day, revenue, orders}...]
deactivate DB
OrdDAO --> DashSvc: daily revenue data
deactivate OrdDAO

' --- KPI 5: Top Events ---
DashSvc -> EvtDAO: getTopEvents(orgId, 5)
activate EvtDAO
EvtDAO -> DB: SELECT TOP 5\n  e.title,\n  COUNT(o.orderId) as orders,\n  SUM(o.totalAmount) as revenue\nFROM Events e\nLEFT JOIN Orders o ON ...\nWHERE e.organizerId = ?\nGROUP BY e.eventId, e.title\nORDER BY revenue DESC
activate DB
DB --> EvtDAO: Top 5 events
deactivate DB
EvtDAO --> DashSvc: topEvents
deactivate EvtDAO

DashSvc --> Controller: OrganizerDashboard {\n  eventStats, revenueStats,\n  ticketStats, dailyRevenue,\n  topEvents\n}
deactivate DashSvc

Controller --> Browser: Forward → organizer/dashboard.jsp\n(all stats + chart data as JSON)
deactivate Controller

Browser -> Browser: Chart.js renders:\n- Bar chart: Revenue/day\n- Doughnut: Event status\n- Line: Ticket sales trend\n- Table: Top 5 events

Browser --> Organizer: 📊 Dashboard với KPIs:\n- 10 sự kiện hoạt động\n- 15,000,000₫ doanh thu\n- 350 vé bán / 180 check-in\n- Charts & Rankings

== Admin Dashboard (tương tự nhưng toàn hệ thống) ==

note over Controller, DB
  Admin Dashboard aggregates
  ALL organizers' data:
  - Total users by role
  - Total events by status
  - System-wide revenue
  - Monthly revenue chart
  - Top organizers by revenue
  - Category distribution (Pie)
end note

@enduml
